Formulate a PHP program to open a text file and print the nth line in the text file if then'th line
does not exist print 'no data'.

CODE:
<?php
function printNthLine($filename, $n) {
    // Open the file for reading
    $file = fopen($filename, "r");

    if (!$file) {
        echo "Unable to open file.";
        return;
    }

    $currentLine = 1;
    $result = "no data";

    // Read file line by line
    while (!feof($file)) {
        $line = fgets($file);
        if ($currentLine == $n) {
            $result = $line;
            break;
        }
        $currentLine++;
    }

    fclose($file);

    echo $result;
}

// Example usage
printNthLine("sample.txt", 3);  // Prints the 3rd line, or 'no data'
?>

OUTPUT:
Warning: fopen(sample.txt): Failed to open stream: No such file or directory in /tmp/XR6oEBPqfb/main.php on line 4
Unable to open file.
